      • sift

        public DTNode<I,D> sift(AccessSequenceProvider<I> asp)
        Sifts an access sequence provided by an object into the tree, starting at the root. This operation performs a "hard" sift, i.e., it will not stop at temporary nodes.
        Parameters:
        asp - the object providing the access sequence
        Returns:
        the leaf resulting from the sift operation

      • sift

        public DTNode<I,D> sift(AccessSequenceProvider<I> asp,
                        boolean hard)
        Sifts an access sequence provided by an object into the tree, starting at the root. This can either be a "soft" sift, which stops either at the leaf or at the first temporary node, or a "hard" sift, stopping only at a leaf.
        Parameters:
        asp - the object providing the access sequence
        hard -
        Returns:
